cs.NE, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SD, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) - The paper proposes a deep cerebellar model articulation controller (DCMAC) for adaptive noise cancellation (ANC) and derives a modified backpropagation training algorithm to learn the DCMAC parameters. This suggests the use of neural networks and machine learning techniques, which are commonly associated with the cs.NE sub-category.
2. cs.LG (Learning) - The paper proposes a deep structure for the CMAC model, which allows for more effective characterization of nonlinear transformations. This suggests a focus on learning and optimization, which are commonly associated with the cs.LG sub-category.
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper proposes a novel approach for ANC using a deep cerebellar model, which is a type of artificial neural network. This suggests a focus on artificial intelligence, which is commonly associated with the cs.AI sub-category.
4. cs.SD (Sound) - The paper focuses on adaptive noise cancellation, which is a common problem in the field of sound processing. This suggests a focus on sound processing, which is commonly associated with the cs.SD sub-category.
5. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper proposes a control system for ANC using the DCMAC model. This suggests a focus on systems and control, which are commonly associated with the cs.SY
